definitions.definition: To bring (something) into practice.
definitions.example: Wheeled transport was introduced long ago.

definitions.definition: A fine fiber excreted by the silkworm or other arthropod (such as a spider).
definitions.example: The thread made of silk was barely visible.

definitions.definition: A fine, soft cloth woven from silk fibers.
Anything which resembles silk, such as the filiform styles of the female flower of maize, or the seed covering of bombaxes.
The gown worn by a Senior (i.e. Queen's/King's) Counsel.
A Senior (i.e. Queen's or King's) Counsel.
(circus arts, in the plural) A pair of long silk sheets suspended in the air on which a performer performs tricks.
(usually in the plural) The garments worn by a jockey displaying the colors of the horse's owner.
To remove the silk from (corn).
An advertising promotion
Of or relating to an advertising promotion; serving to promote a service, institution, business, etc.
definitions.example: Collect five promotional vouchers to claim your prize.

definitions.definition: Of or relating to promotion to a post of higher status.
A very young human, particularly from birth to a couple of years old or until walking is fully mastered.

Any very young animal, especially a vertebrate; many species have specific names for their babies, such as kittens for the babies of cats, puppies for the babies of dogs, and chickens for the babies of birds. See for more.
Unborn young; a fetus.
definitions.example: When is your baby due?

definitions.definition: A person who is immature, infantile or feeble.
definitions.example: Stand up for yourself – don't be such a baby!

definitions.definition: A person who is new to or inexperienced in something.
definitions.example: I only qualified as an architect this summer, so I'm still a baby.

definitions.definition: The lastborn of a family; the youngest sibling, irrespective of age.
definitions.example: Adam is the baby of the family.

definitions.definition: A term of endearment used to refer to or address one's girlfriend, boyfriend or spouse.
definitions.example: Baby, don't cry.

definitions.definition: A form of address to a man or a woman considered to be attractive.
definitions.example: Hey baby, what are you doing later?

definitions.definition: A pet project or responsibility.
definitions.example: You need to talk to John about that – it's his baby.

definitions.definition: An affectionate term for anything.
definitions.example: See my new car here? I can't wait to take this baby for a drive.

definitions.definition: A small image of an infant; a doll.
To coddle; to pamper somebody like an infant.
To tend (something) with care; to be overly attentive to (something), fuss over.
A bisexual person.
A type of jade disk produced in ancient China.
Bisexual.
definitions.example: I'm straight, but my oldest sister is bi.

definitions.definition: To put together; to assemble; to make by gathering things from various sources.
definitions.example: Samuel Johnson compiled one of the most influential dictionaries of the English language.

definitions.definition: To construct, build.
To use a compiler to process source code and produce executable code.
definitions.example: After I compile this program I'll run it and see if it works.

definitions.definition: To be successfully processed by a compiler into executable code.
definitions.example: There must be an error in my source code because it won't compile.

definitions.definition: To contain or comprise.
To write; to compose.
Of or dealing with languages or cultures derived from Roman influence and Latin: Italian, French, Portuguese, Spanish, Romanian, Catalan, Occitan, Corsican, etc.
Of or pertaining to Romance.
Of or pertaining to Romanticism.
Of a work of literature, a writer etc.: being like or having the characteristics of a romance, or poetic tale of a mythic or quasi-historical time; fantastic.
Fictitious, imaginary.
Fantastic, unrealistic (of an idea etc.); fanciful, sentimental, impractical (of a person).
definitions.example: Mary sighed, knowing her ideals were far too romantic to work in reality.

definitions.definition: Having the qualities of romance (in the sense of something appealing deeply to the imagination); invoking on a powerfully sentimental idea of life; evocative, atmospheric.
Pertaining to an idealised form of love (originally, as might be felt by the heroes of a romance); conducive to romance; loving, affectionate.
definitions.example: Their kiss started casually, but it slowly turned romantic.

definitions.definition: A person with romantic character (a character like those of the knights in a mythic romance).
A person who is behaving romantically (in a manner befitting someone who feels an idealized form of love).
definitions.example: Oh, flowers! You're such a romantic.

definitions.definition: To uncover; to show and display that which was hidden.
To communicate that which could not be known or discovered without divine or supernatural instruction.
Of or pertaining to the revelations of a divinity to humankind.
Someone who is an expert in, or devoted to, some specific branch of study or research.
A physician whose practice is limited to a particular branch of medicine or surgery.
Any of several non-commissioned ranks corresponding to that of corporal.
An organism that is specialized for a particular environment.
definitions.example: The tree Lepidothamnus laxifolius is a high alpine specialist found in high-altitude bog communities and in scrub.
